,Recommended,477170,23494243,"Posted: 10 June, 2016",all,ZiXT,"Yes, the concept and many mechanics are borrowed liberally from Xortex, but this expands on it to make it a more replayable gameChamber 19 encourages moving around your playspace to a greater extent than does Xortex.  There's a good variety of different enemy types, and the waves can get quite challenging.Xortex seems like a tech demo/minigame, while Chamber 19 feels like fairly well-rounded casual game.Price may be a bit steep, and the graphics aren't quite to the level of Xortex, but still worth it for the amount of fun to be had jumping in for a random game.Highly recommended if you enjoyed Xortex or bullet-hell games in general."
