76561198039364157,Recommended,477170,23699245,"Posted: 21 June, 2016",all,daymaster,"Chamber 19 is an excellent bullet hell vr shooter.You fight increasingly difficult waves of enemies with a ship you hold in your hand, exactly like Xortex. The game introduces new enemies at an acceptable pace, giving you time to get better throughout a single playthrough.There are a few different power ups, some that spawn when enemies are killed and a choice of 4 powerful upgrades after defeating a boss.I like the second drone upgrade, allowed me to score #4 on the global leaderboards.Missile upgrade kind of sucks, I find the missiles loop too much and your stuck unable to fire at targets right in your face. I would prefer rapid fire micro-missiles over the current giant mess that they are. It's very distracting.The bosses are good, however I feel the first and second bosses are far more difficult then the next 2. Not sure how to beat wave 30 though, that thing scared me.I like the new options recently added, the 180 mode is a far superior experience.Just a note that I got major slowdown around wave 27-29 with a GTX 1080, so definitely some optimization is needed.Overall I recommend this game to anyone who liked Xortex."
